# projectedValue

**Instance Property**

A projection of the state object that creates bindings to its properties.

## Declaration

```swift
@MainActor @preconcurrency var projectedValue: ObservedObject<ObjectType>.Wrapper { get }
```

## Discussion

Use the projected value to get a [doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/Binding] to a property of a state object. To access the projected value, prefix the property name with a dollar sign (`$`). For example, you can get a binding to a model’s `isEnabled` Boolean so that a [doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/Toggle] can control the value:

```swift
struct MyView: View {
    @StateObject private var model = DataModel()

    var body: some View {
        Toggle("Enabled", isOn: $model.isEnabled)
    }
}
```



## Getting the value

- **wrappedValue**: The underlying value referenced by the state object.
